                <div class="card-header rounded-0 text-light bg-dark bold">Introduction to Media Literacy</div>
                <div class="card-body rounded-0 indent table-info">
                    <p>Media Literacy is the ability of a person to distinguish different forms of media, identify its roles in culture,
					and think critically about the information obtained and the message of it. 
					While Information Literacy is one’s capability to assess, understand, make use of, and 
					distinguish if the information is reliable or not, which can help in problem solving situations, 
					decision making, and the acquisition of knowledge. Technology literacy is one’s capability to use technology to assess, 
					create and communicate information. These forms of literacy are connected to one another since you get information from the media, 
					and you use technology in order to create media. These can affect society by giving free and easy access to information to everyone. 
					This however can cause implications too as it is also easy to create fake information, giving confusion, and discourse among the masses. 
					But if done properly, everyone can reliably obtain proper information if they are capable of assessing what information 
					they get instead of taking it at face value.</p>            
                    
                </div>
