                            <h2 id="whatismedia">What Is Media?</h2>
                            <p class="pb-3 bold">
                                We encounter media frequently in our lives, but what exactly is media? What should we be aware about it?
                            </p>                     
                    </div>
                    <hr>
                    <p class="pb-3 indent">
                        Media is a way of spreading information, be it digitally, physically (with the use of paper), or via audio (using radio and the like); it can affect people positively or negatively which can depend on the information they receive. I see it as a valuable source for current news but it may not be fully trust worthy so I take information that I get from common media with some doubts until I do more research about the topic.
                    </p>
                    <p class="pb-3 indent">
                        Media technologies have the power to transform culture since it spreads not only information, but ideological messages or propaganda. And with our current use of media, it is also possible to be influenced by the culture of others from interacting with them through the internet mainly with twitter and the like. With the connections created from this according to Galarneau, L. (2017), things such as Support, Creativity, Diversity and many more can be some of the things that help transform the culture of the people, which can also shape culture. Although, social media can have negative effects to one’s development of culture as it is common for harassment and cyber bullying to occur.
                    </p>
					<p class="pb-3 indent">
                        Media also has large impact in politics as due to the interaction in social media, they can be influenced by other’s culture and beliefs, changing their views about politics and can sometimes be manipulated in some form to cause discourse among the people. An example of this is with the occurrence of radicalized jihadist youth due to the use of media to convert their ideals, according to Furedi, F.(2017).
                    </p>

                    <hr>
